Filename: fontanvil
Title: FontAnvil
Title[ja]: ＦｏｎｔＡｎｖｉｌ
Subtitle: Font-editing script interpreter from the Tsukurimashou Project
Subtitle[ja]: 『作りましょうプロジェクト』からフォントのエディットする言語
Main-Text.
<P>FontAnvil is a script language interpreter for manipulating fonts. 
FontAnvil is substantially compatible with the <A
HREF="http://fontforge.github.io/en-US/">PfaEdit/FontForge</A> native
scripting language, but FontAnvil is intended for non-interactive use; for
instance, invocation from the build systems of font packages like
Tsukurimashou.  To better serve font package build systems in general and
Tsukurimashou in particular, FontAnvil has no GUI and, to a reasonable
extent, avoids dependencies on external packages.</P>

<P>Read the <A HREF="fontanvil.pdf">FontAnvil user's manual</A> (PDF).</P>

<P>Use of FontAnvil on Windows is not officially supported, and the
Tsukurimashou Project does not provide official binary packages of FontAnvil
for any platform.  Only the source code is officially supported, and only
under Linux and Mac.  However, a user has graciously contributed some
<A HREF="http://sourceforge.net/projects/fontforgebuilds/files/fontanvil/">unofficial
binary packages</A> for Windows.</P>
